<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D67FF80FF4DFAF2FDF1FAEF" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="207B96733D67FF80FF4DFAF2FDF1FAEF" blockId="20.[151,1437,1230,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FF4DFAF2FEA5FAC3" bold="true" box="[199,334,1339,1365]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronym in honor of Dr. Norman Platnick, for his contribution to taxonomy of the spiders of the world.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D67FF80FF4DFA4BFF11F9B9" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D67FF80FF4DFA4BFF11F9B9" blockId="20.[151,1437,1230,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FF4DFA4BFEA9FA0A" bold="true" box="[199,322,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D67FF80FE25FA4AFD86FA0B" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[431,621,1411,1437]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platnicki" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FE25FA4AFD86FA0B" box="[431,621,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Patrera platnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FDF9FA4AFD5BFA0B" bold="true" box="[627,688,1411,1437]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D67FF80FDF9FA4AFD5BFA0B" box="[627,688,1411,1437]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D67FF80FC0AFA4AFBFAFA0B" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[896,1041,1411,1437]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbacoas" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FC0AFA4AFBFAFA0B" box="[896,1041,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. barbacoas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FB9DFA4AFBBFFA0B" bold="true" box="[1047,1108,1411,1437]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D67FF80FB9DFA4AFBBFFA0B" box="[1047,1108,1411,1437]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by having the abdomen with several dark patches and subsquare retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D67FF80FCEAFA6EFC5FFA55" box="[864,948,1447,1475]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[160,1422,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-148@13.[151,1436,561,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5A–D. Patrera barbacoas n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10604): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468393/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
̅D), but can be diagnosed by their large and apically squared retrolateral tibial apophysis (smaller and thinner in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D67FF80FC06FA02FBF6FA73" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[908,1053,1483,1509]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbacoas">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FC06FA02FBF6FA73" box="[908,1053,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. barbacoas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and embolus inserted subbasally on the tegulum with rounded base (basally originating on the tegulum and with narrow base in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D67FF80FB4EFA26FABDF99F" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1220,1366,1519,1545]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbacoas">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FB4EFA26FABDF99F" box="[1220,1366,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. barbacoas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D67FF80FAE5FA26FF2CF9B9" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1479,1503]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,181,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-27@22.[151,1436,181,1455]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10A–D. Patrera platnicki n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-5673): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468403/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
̅D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D67FF81FF4DF9FFFB61FF43" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D67FF81FF4DF9FFFB61FF43" blockId="20.[151,1437,1230,2013]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FF4DF9FFFEB2F9C6" bold="true" box="[199,345,1590,1616]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D67FF80FEE9F9FEFE4FF9C7" box="[355,420,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Male.</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D67FF80FE3CF9FEFDC8F9C7" box="[438,547,1591,1617]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-5673). Carapace brown, darker on the cephalic region and thoracic groove (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D67FF80FF7FF992FEB6F9E3" box="[245,349,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1479,1503]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,181,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-27@22.[151,1436,181,1455]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10A–D. Patrera platnicki n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-5673): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468403/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae dark brown. Labium and endites brown. Sternum brown. Legs yellow, darkest from tibiae to tarsi. Abdomen grayish with very black setae, and four black posterior transversal bands; ventrally yellow. Spinnerets yellow (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D67FF80FEFBF96AFE31F92B" box="[369,474,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1479,1503]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,181,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-27@22.[151,1436,181,1455]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10A–D. Patrera platnicki n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-5673): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468403/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Total length 8.55, carapace length 3.69, width 3.22, high 1.49. Clypeus height 0.07. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.15, ALE 0.22, PME 0.2, PLE 0.3; AME–AME 0.34, AME–ALE 0.49, PME–PME 0.56, PME–PLE 0.54, ALE–PLE 0.56. Chelicerae 1.9 long, five promarginal teeth, six retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: leg I—femur 5.02/ patella 1.79/ tibia 5.19/ metatarsus 4.25/ tarsus 2.48 /total 18.73; II—4.68/ 1.69/ 4.84/ 4.08/ 2.34/ 17.63; III—3.4/ 0.82/ 2.52/ 2.79/ 1.22/ 10.75; IV—4.18/ 1.2/ 3.48/ 3.84/ 1.5/ 14.2. Leg spination: I—metatarsus v1-0-1, p0-1-0, r0-1-0; II—metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-1-0, r0-1-0; III—tibia p1-0-1, r1-0- 1, metatarsus p1-2-2, r1-2-2; IV—tibia p1-0-1, r0-1-1, metatarsus p1-2-2, r1-2-2. Abdomen: length 4.29, epigastric furrow 1.02 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.0 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis large, apically square and apically serrate; cymbium longer than tibia; subtegulum longer than wide with subrounded distal projection; tegulum longer than wide; median apophysis very short, curved and basally situated; embolus long, thin with rounded base, apically filiform and subbasally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D66FF81FC7EFF72FBAFFF43" box="[1012,1092,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1479,1503]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,181,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-27@22.[151,1436,181,1455]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10A–D. Patrera platnicki n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-5673): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468403/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
B–D).
</paragraph>
